# Environment Variables

## Frontend (Vite)

# Supabase Configuration
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here

# Optional: Sentry for error tracking
VITE_SENTRY_DSN=
VITE_SENTRY_ENVIRONMENT=development

## Backend (Supabase Edge Functions)

# OpenAI API Key (set via Supabase secrets, not in .env)
# Run: npx supabase secrets set OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-openai-api-key

## Deprecated (Legacy - No longer needed with Agents SDK)

# OpenAI Assistant ID (used by old Assistant v2 architecture)
# Not needed for Agents SDK - kept for backwards compatibility
# VITE_OPENAI_ASSISTANT_ID=asst-...

## Notes

- Frontend variables must start with `VITE_` to be available in the browser
- Never commit real API keys to version control
- Use Supabase secrets for sensitive backend environment variables
- See ARCHITECTURE.md for more details on the current Agents SDK architecture
